# Figma — Paul design file

This project is linked to the **Paul** Figma file via the Figma MCP server.

## File

- **Name:** Paul
- **URL:** https://www.figma.com/design/354mOGQ3VC3WZmyGVp06kg/Paul
- **File key:** `354mOGQ3VC3WZmyGVp06kg`
- **Default page:** `0:1` (Page 1)

## Stack alignment

When implementing designs from Figma into this repo:

- React 19 + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS v4 (`tailwind.config.ts` breakpoints: xs 320, sm 425, md 768, lg 1024, xl 1440, 2xl 2550)
- Adapt Figma MCP reference output to existing project structure under `src/`

## Project structure

```
src/
  assets/           # Static assets, organized by page or shared scope
    homepage/       # Homepage-specific images
    icons/          # Shared icons
  components/
    layout/         # Navbar, Footer, etc.
    ui/             # Reusable UI primitives (Button, SectionBadge, …)
  pages/
    home/           # One folder per page
      HomePage.tsx
      components/   # Page-specific section components
      data/         # Page content / constants
```

- Keep assets separate under `src/assets/` (never inline remote Figma URLs in production code).
- Each page gets its own folder under `src/pages/`.
- Shared layout lives in `src/components/layout/`; reusable UI in `src/components/ui/`.

## MCP workflow

- **Design → code:** `get_design_context` with `fileKey` + `nodeId` (convert `-` to `:` in node IDs, e.g. `0-1` → `0:1`)
- **Structure overview:** `get_metadata` with `fileKey`
- **Screenshots:** `get_screenshot`
- **Code → design / edits:** `use_figma` (load `figma-use` skill first)
